{
  "stem": "17526.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 302.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And this happened every day on the street, so everybody tried to obey and be a good person, not to get shot.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They issued lists and those lists, they had to deliver to so many people.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "These people were hauled away to the labor camps.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "These-- these labor camps were an arm of the Wehrmacht, which is the German Army, and there were some of them worked in munition factories, some of them worked in other installations which were vital for the war-- German war machine.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And later on, these very same people built the crematories, built Auschwitz, Oswiencim.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "These very same labor camps built Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Now, Auschwitz was a small town, it's called Oswiencim and it spells O-S-W-I-E-N-C-I-M, Oswiencim.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The Germans Germanized-- they-- they-- they changed all the Polish names into German.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Like Bendin became Bensberg.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Bensberg.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Oswiencim became Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "This town was about 40 kilometers from Bendin, and for some-- I don't know for why reason, for what reason, they built these big camps.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "First it was a labor camp and then they build the crematoriums.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And Brzezinka, Birkenau-- Birkenau, which is three kilometers from Auschwitz, was a little town called Brzezinka, B-R-Z-E-Z-I-N-K-A.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "It was named Birkenau, B-I-R-K-E-N-A-U, Birkenau.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Birkenau was actually the death factory.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Auschwitz was a labor camp that was converted into a concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Naturally, this was not the only camp and-- but in our area, this happened to be the camp.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Later on, it become one of the most concentrated, so much so that 1 and 1/2 million people were burned in Auschwitz. 1 and 1/2 million people, you're talking about millions.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
